column3: Can you say for certain that the bullets marked as  P-4 had been fired  from P-l?
Is there a possibility that its particular P-4 could have exited from  another T56 type gun?
Do you in this case say that particular P-4 had exited from the gun P-l?
Do you say that those did not exit out of any other T56 type gun?
What is  the reason for  you to say certainly?
It is  because  the  exterior appearance of the  empty caps P-4  and  the  exterior appearance  of
the bullets that exited from P-l were matching when they were examined."
The  witnesses  above  evidence  on  his  findings  were  unchallenged  before  the  High  Court,  and
therefore  we  see  no  reason  to  reject  the  above  findings  of the  Government  Analyst.  The  learned
